.TH "nsm_get_handle" 9 "nsm_get_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nsm_get_handle \- Find or create a cached nsm_handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct nsm_handle *" nsm_get_handle
.BI "(const struct net *net "  ","
.BI "const struct sockaddr *sap "  ","
.BI "const size_t salen "  ","
.BI "const char *hostname "  ","
.BI "const size_t hostname_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
network namespace
.IP "sap" 12
pointer to socket address of handle to find
.IP "salen" 12
length of socket address
.IP "hostname" 12
pointer to C string containing hostname to find
.IP "hostname_len" 12
length of C string
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Behavior is modulated by the global nsm_use_hostnames variable.

Returns a cached nsm_handle after bumping its ref count, or
returns a fresh nsm_handle if a handle that matches \fIsap\fP and/or
\fIhostname\fP cannot be found in the handle cache.  Returns NULL if
an error occurs.
